## M20a.1 negative: sigil-prefixed parameter on a non-`self` name.
##
## `?xs` and `!other` etc. are reserved for the `?self` / `!self`
## sugar only. For other parameters, the sigil belongs on the type:
## `xs: ?[]Item`, `other: !User`, etc. This rule defends against the
## foot-gun where users assume `?name` is a general "borrowed param"
## form.
##
## EXPECTED: sema error at the bad parameter.

fun first(?xs) -> Int
  42

sub main()
  print(first(1))
